[TestFeaturesCheck/buildinfo_unsupported_still_reports_problem - 1]
- description: buildinfo unsupported still reports problem
  content: |
    - record: foo
      expr: mad_over_time(bar[5m])
  output: |
    2 |   expr: mad_over_time(bar[5m])
                ^^^^^^^^^^^^^ `mad_over_time` was added in Prometheus 2.49.0 and requires `--enable-feature=promql-experimental-functions` to be set on `prom` Prometheus server at https://simple.example.com.
  problem:
    reporter: promql/features
    summary: required feature flag not enabled
    details: |-
        This query uses PromQL features that require feature flags to be enabled on the Prometheus server via `--enable-feature=...` flag.
        [Click here](https://prometheus.io/docs/prometheus/latest/feature_flags/) to see Prometheus feature flags documentation.
    diagnostics:
        - message: '`mad_over_time` was added in Prometheus 2.49.0 and requires `--enable-feature=promql-experimental-functions` to be set on `prom` Prometheus server at https://simple.example.com.'
          firstcolumn: 1
          lastcolumn: 13
          kind: 0
    lines:
        first: 2
        last: 2
    severity: 2
    anchor: 0

